Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with community detection in networks, specifically in on-line social networks, which falls under the scope of cs.SI.
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a new model and estimation procedure for community detection, which can be considered as a software engineering problem.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses spectral clustering and develops consistent and computationally efficient estimators, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with modeling and analyzing continuous-time networks, which can be considered as a systems and control problem.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new model and estimation procedure for analyzing large networks, which can be considered as a data structures and algorithms problem.
